── Potential V(χ) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  V(χ)   = V_0*exp(-\alpha*\chi/M_P)
  V'(χ)  = -V_0*\alpha*exp(-\alpha*\chi/M_P)/M_P

── Slow-roll EOS derivation (ξ=0 baseline) ──────────────────────────
  χ̇²/V (slow-roll) = \alpha**2/3

── Scherrer-Sen baseline relation ───────────────────────────────────
  1 + w₀ = α²/3   (Scherrer-Sen 2008, exponential potential)

  α(w₀) = sqrt(3(1+w₀)) = sqrt(3*w_0 + 3)

── Scherrer-Sen w_a (ξ=0) ───────────────────────────────────────────
  w_a ≃ -24*w_0/7 - 24/7

── NMC correction to 1+w₀ (first order in ξ_χ) ─────────────────────
  δ(1+w₀)/(1+w₀) = -8*\chi*\xi_\chi/(M_P*\alpha)

  ξ-correction factor δ_ξ = 8ξχ / (αM_P)  with α→√(3(1+w₀))
  δ_ξ = 8*sqrt(3)*\chi*\xi_\chi/(3*M_P*sqrt(w_0 + 1))

── w_a formula at first order in ξ_χ (D4 KEY RESULT) ───────────────

  Baseline (Scherrer-Sen 2008):
    w_a^SS = −(24/7)(1 + w₀)

  With NMC coupling ξ_χ (first order):
    w_a = −(24/7)(1 + w₀) × [1 + δ_ξ]

  where:
    δ_ξ = 8 ξ_χ χ / (α M_P)  =  8 ξ_χ χ / (√(3(1+w₀)) M_P)

  In terms of ε ≡ ξ_χ χ²/M_P²  and  α = √(3(1+w₀)):
    δ_ξ = 8 √ε / α  =  8 √ε / √(3(1+w₀))   [if ξ>0]

  Physical interpretation:
    ξ > 0 (positive NMC): δ_ξ > 0 → |w_a| reduced (thawing slowed)
    ξ < 0 (negative NMC): δ_ξ < 0 → |w_a| enhanced (phantom tendency)

── Numerical check (ξ_χ=0.1, χ=M_P, w₀=−0.9) ──────────────────────
  α = √(3×0.1) = 0.5477
  w_a^SS        = -0.3429
  δ_ξ           = 1.4606
  w_a^NMC       = -0.8436
  Relative shift = -146.1 %

── LaTeX (paste into paper) ─────────────────────────────────────────
  w_a = -\frac{24}{7}(1+w_0)\left[1 + \frac{8\xi_\chi\chi}{\alpha M_P}\right]

  \delta_\xi \equiv \frac{8\xi_\chi\chi}{\alpha M_P}
            = \frac{8\xi_\chi\chi}{\sqrt{3(1+w_0)}\,M_P}

Status: FUNCTIONAL — w_a formula at order ξ_χ derived analytically.
